<TEXT>
the arizona republic the roanoke 
times and world news and newsweek magazine were among top winners 
in the 1989 national headliners awards announced this week in this 
seaside resort 
the arizona republic received the award for outstanding 
investigative reporting for a series of stories examining the use 
and misuse of drugs on elderly people the stories were written by 
mike masterson and chuck cook 
mary bishop of the roanoke times and world news won the 
outstanding public service award for poison in our homes a 
series on exterminators and the effects of little regulation of the 
industry 
newsweek magazines coverage of the presidential election 
received the award for outstanding coverage of a major news event 
for magazines and syndicates newsweek writer bill carol also was 
cited for his consistently outstanding feature writing for a 
magazine or syndicate 
other firstplace winners include 
outstanding news reporting by a newspaper circulation to 
50000 david gomez and patricia guthrie the albuquerque tribune 
gallup the alcohol problems in gallup nm 
outstanding news reporting by a newspaper circulation 50000 
to 150000 anchorage daily news staff alaska natives a people 
in peril 
outstanding news reporting by a newspaper circulation over 
150000 louisville courierjournal staff for coverage of the 
carrollton ky bus crash 
consistently outstanding local interest column roger simon 
the baltimore sun 
consistently outstanding column on one subject jim dwyer 
newsday in the subways 
consistently outstanding editorial cartoons walt handelsman 
the scranton times 
outstanding spot news photography ron olshwanger st louis 
postdispatch for photo of a baby rescued from fire 
outstanding feature photography ben desoto houston chronicle 
for photo of cowboy choreography 
outstanding sports photography brian smith miami herald for 
photo of diver greg louganis hitting the board 
consistently outstanding sports writing terry egan the times 
heraldrecord middletown ny 
consistently outstanding feature writing daniel golden the 
boston globe 
consistently outstanding column by a magazine or syndicate 
judith stone discover magazine 
outstanding spot news photo by a magazine or syndicate ramazan 
ozturk time magazine for photo of mustard gas attack victims 
outstanding feature photo by a magazine or syndicate jeff 
widener associated press for photo of a man cleaning skulls titled 
the killing field 
outstanding sports photo by a magazine or syndicate dieter 
endlicher associated press for photo of a track star titled the 
fastest woman 
winners in the broadcast categories will be announced later this 
month the awards weekend will be june 2 and 3 in atlantic city 
the national headliners awards now in its 55th year are 
sponsored by the press club of atlantic city 
