petty crime in the brussels subway has 
increased 26fold in the 1980s but the metro remains among the 
safest subway systems in the world transit authorities say 
thefts of purses money and jewelry in the trains and in the 
subways 57 stations surged to over 800 cases last year from 30 in 
1980 these and other petty crimes were 266 times as high last year 
as in 1980 
but officials said friday that no murder or rape has ever been 
committed in the subway system which is used by 650000 people each 
day 
subway vandalism also was reported on the rise in 1988 the 
subway system spent 100000 repairing damage by graffiti writers 
and vandals 
