<TEXT>
a small twinengine plane slammed into a 
twostory building in a lima suburb killing the eight american 
tourists and two peruvians aboard the us embassy said saturday 
the plane owned by the privately owned aerocondor airline 
crashed into a partially constructed building in heavy fog friday 
evening witnesses said the engines were sputtering before the plane 
slammed into the building which belongs to the university of san 
martin de porras 
the eight tourists and peruvian pilot and copilot were killed 
the embassy said a man at the construction site was injured police 
said 
the embassy identified the americans as 
john howe 81 and his wife barbara 72 of hagerstown md 
robert fisher 66 and his wife ruth 62 of moorestown nj 
dorothy menzies 77 and her daughter virginia fennel 48 of 
hickory nc 
virginia hall 78 and her granddaughter mary shuford 28 
also of hickory nc 
investigators have not said what caused the accident 
an official for aerocondor speaking on condition of anonymity 
said the plane was returning after having flown over the famous 
nazca lines 250 miles southeast of the capital 
the nazca lines are giant precolumbian drawings on the desert 
believed to represent a primitive calendar 
