<TEXT>
in the aftermath of the senates rejection of 
former texas sen john tower for secretary of defense republican 
punsters grumbled that their nominee had been brought down by a 
relatively new phenomenon nunnpartisanship 
the play on words a part snide and part comical reference to 
sen sen nunn underscored both the pivotal role the georgia 
democrat played in the struggle over the tower nomination and the 
irony that nunns influence in a partisan battle stemmed largely 
from his reputation as the senates bipartisan defense expert 
nunn chairman of the senate armed services committee said when 
the tower debate began that he expected some permanent bruises 
before it was all over 
and for the first time in his 16year senate career as the 
debate raged throughout last week unn heard republican colleagues 
hurl heated and repeated charges of partisanship in his direction 
this goes into the memory banks senate minority leader bob 
dole of kansas said after singling out nunn for special criticism 
following towers defeat 
but while the tower fight may have tarnished nunns reputation 
for nonpartisanship political observers say his stature within the 
national democratic party has been enhanced 
with a number of moderate to moderateliberal democrats this 
will increase his influence kevin phillips a republican 
political analyst said in an interview friday 
he has chits with them that he may actually be able to cash in 
for what some people would think of as more responsible defense 
policy phillips said this gives him leverage to pull hitherto 
nondefense democrats into a more defense posture 
william schneider a political analyst with the american 
enterprise institute said nunns role in the tower fight will move 
him onto center stage in national democratic party politics 
within his party he will probably have more clout because he 
delivered schneider said he delivered a real punch to the 
president of the united states 
hes enhanced his image of power as a national democratic 
player and as someone who delivers he said on the other hand 
there is obviously a downside hes sacrificed some of the 
bipartisan appeal he had in the past 
both before and during the tower debate republicans accused nunn 
of using the battle to increase his control over us defense policy 
and to launch his bid for the democratic presidential nomination in 
1992 
nunn repeatedly denied any such motivations saying his actions 
were being questioned simply because he had the evidence on his side 
and was leading the fight against tower 
schneider said he has seen nothing to suggest that nunn was 
motivated by a desire to dominate national defense policy or to 
enhance his presidential prospects 
but if he does want either one of those things the tower fight 
has helped both of those ambitions he said hes more of a 
player in national security policy and hes more of a figure in 
democratic party politics no question about it 
theres also little question that the controversy over the tower 
nomination has changed the way nunn is viewed in the senate the 
hard feelings generated by the fight as doles comment suggests 
wont soon be forgotten 
the difficulty for nunn and the difficulty for everybody else 
is going to be that it is a whole new ball game phillips said 
its not the old ball game that sam nunn had been playing in that 
he had scored very well in 
this is a new national ball game and its going to be a 
different one and its going to have its share of unpleasantness 
said phillips 
