we have calls coming in from all over i understand there will 
be charter buses from all over the united states police capt ted 
panning said saturday 
he said between 5000 and 60000 people were expected to converge 
on tickfaw a town of 500 about 45 miles north of new orleans 
their destination was a field where a wooden cross has been 
erected beside a mobile home belonging to alfredo raimondo raimondo 
says the virgin mary appeared to him in chalmette a new orleans 
suburb and told him to go to tickfaw to honor st joseph 
the site is located between the antioch baptist church and the 
sisters of st benedict monastery the pilgrims planned to celebrate 
mass outdoors have a candlelight procession and pray the rosary 
said robbi mayfield a pilgrimage organizer 
panning said as many as 50 law enforcement officers would be on 
hand to help guide traffic and keep cars moving 
were going to try to be as understanding as possible 
panning said 
mayfield who owns a shop that sells religious items in 
chalmette said everyone wanted to know when the virgin mary would 
appear 
i dont know whats going to happen at tickfaw i dont know if 
she intends to appear i just know that she wants us to be there 
mayfield said 
raimondo and his wife are natives of italy but have lived in 
