hundreds of thousands of refugees have fled battle areas and an 
international relief program under united nations auspices hopes to 
transport 170000 tons of food and supplies to distribution points 
before the rainy season starts in may 
but there has been no agreement between relief organizers and 
leaders of the rebels sudan peoples liberation army spla on 
shipments of the supplies in previous years spla forces have fired 
at planes and trucks carrying relief supplies saying the army was 
using them to transport equipment to its troops 
there are some 225 million people in southern sudan last year 
it is estimated that as many as 500000 perished from warrelated 
causes with many starving in isolated villages 
