time to study a proposed month of tranquility which would 
virtually amount to a ceasefire to move relief supplies into 
position 
grant spoke with reporters after meeting prime minister sadek 
mahdi and informing him about the talks with the rebels mahdis 
government has accepted the relief plan 
the spla took a strong position that there was a need for food 
and that they would work to get it to their people grant said 
we have yet to receive a formal reply 
we are going to work with the assumption that we will get 
agreement if not on a month of tranquility then at the very least 
on bubbles of tranquility for the eight points in the plan he 
said 
