jr an american airlines vice president in the 1970s and 
early1980s who now practices law in new york 
how did lorenzo the 48yearold son of spanish immigrants 
manage to build texas air from a tiny intrastate flier mockingly 
dubbed tree top airlines into the nations largest carrier 
