<TEXT>
subaru of america announced friday it 
will voluntarily recall 15000 justy fourwheeldrive vehicles 
because of transmission fluid problems that can cause the rear 
wheels to lock 
the vehicles subject to recall are those manufactured for the 
1988 and 1989 model years before march 10 1989 said spokesman 
steve davis 
insufficient levels of transmission fluid may result because of 
incorrect fluid level prescribed by subaru the checking procedure 
described in the owners manual and the design of the fluid 
dipstick davis said 
low fluid level can cause ball bearing seizure and possible 
rearwheel lockup he said 
there were a few cars where customers had rearwheel lockup 
because of the bearing seizure davis said no accidents or any 
bodily injuries were associated with that just mechanical damage 
were bringing these cars in and actually raising the level of 
fluid in the transmission davis said 
in addition a modified dipstick will be installed and an insert 
for the owners manual describing correct transmission fluid 
checking procedures will be provided at no cost to the owner he 
said 
all affected owners will be notified by mail the company said 
the problem does not affect the twowheel drive justy davis said 
